timeseries

Class TimePeriod

  • java.lang.Object
    • TimePeriod

  • public final class TimePeriod
extends Object
    An amount of time expressed in a particular time unit. This class wraps a TimeUnit together with a positive integer period length, allowing one to create a wide range of different time periods. This class is immutable and thread-safe.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TimePeriod

        public TimePeriod(TimeUnit timeUnit,
                  long periodLength)
        Create a new time period with the given unit of time and period length.
        Parameters:
        timeUnit - the unit of time underlying this time period
        periodLength - the length of this time period relative to the given unit of time. Note the periodLength argument must be a long. Most decimal time periods can be modeled by converting to an appropriate time unit with a smaller order of magnitude. For example, the halfMonth() constructor works by converting 15.2184375 days to 1314873 seconds.

      • frequencyPer

        public double frequencyPer(TimePeriod otherTimePeriod)
        Compute and return the number of times this time period occurs in the given time period.

        For example, if this time period is a month and the given time period is half a year, the return value is 6 since a month occurs 6 times in one year.

        Parameters:
        otherTimePeriod - the time period for which the frequency of occurrence of this time period is to be found.
        Returns:
        the number of times this time period occurs in the provided time period.
